# shadcn/ui Component Library - STRICT ENFORCEMENT

This project uses **EXCLUSIVELY** shadcn/ui for ALL UI elements. **NO CUSTOM UI COMPONENTS ARE ALLOWED.**

## ABSOLUTE RULES - NO EXCEPTIONS

1. **NEVER create custom UI elements** - Always use shadcn/ui components
2. **NEVER use raw HTML elements** for UI (div, button, input, etc.)
3. **NEVER use custom CSS classes** for styling - use shadcn/ui variants and compositions
4. **NEVER create custom styled components** - use existing shadcn/ui components
5. **If a component doesn't exist in shadcn/ui, install it first**

## Initial Setup

If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest create
```

## Adding Components

When you need ANY UI element that's not installed, you MUST use:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

