## Enforcement Rules

1. **Before creating ANY UI element**, check if shadcn/ui has it
2. **If it exists in shadcn/ui**, install and use it
3. **If it doesn't exist**, compose existing components
4. **NEVER create custom UI** under any circumstances
5. **Use `mode="modal"` for ALL Clerk authentication components**

## Violations Will Be Rejected

Any code containing:
- Raw HTML elements for UI (div, button, input, etc.)
- Custom CSS classes for styling
- Custom styled components
- Non-shadcn/ui UI libraries
- Clerk components without `mode="modal"`

**Will be immediately rejected and must be rewritten using shadcn/ui components.**